msg: * The new version of the JMS transport requires knowledge of the message content type (see SYNAPSE-304). Since the client doesn't send a Content-Type header, the transport.jms.ContentType property must be used.
* Removed an incorrect statement in the document saying that the proxy sends back a reply using a temporary queue. Indeed, the operation is out-only.
